N:playwriter
D:Playwright CLI+MCP connecting to your running Chrome browser (existing logins/cookies/extensions preserved). Session-based stateful automation via -e flag or MCP execute tool. Use when you need authenticated browser control without re-logging in.
G:playwright browser-automation chrome-extension mcp stateful authenticated session-based aria-ref snapshot

U[5]:
  Automate websites that require login without re-authenticating
  Control real browser tabs with full Playwright API and existing cookies
  Run MCP-based browser automation from Claude Desktop or AI agents
  Execute multi-step stateful flows (shopping carts, multi-page forms, SPAs)
  Record browser sessions or remote-control Chrome on another machine

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Surface,Choose playwriter only when existing Chrome state matters; route isolated or CI-friendly work to agent-browser
  2,Install,Install the extension and turn the target tab green; install CLI with npm install -g playwriter or validate via npx playwriter@latest --help
  3,Session,playwriter session new → creates isolated stateful sandbox; playwriter session list to inspect active sessions
  4,Observe,playwriter -s 1 -e 'await page.goto("https://example.com")'; playwriter -s 1 -e 'await snapshot({ page })'
  5,Act,playwriter -s 1 -e 'await page.locator("aria-ref=e5").click()' then re-snapshot before the next action
  6,MCP,Add {"command":"npx","args":["-y","playwriter@latest"]}; for remote use PLAYWRITER_HOST and PLAYWRITER_TOKEN via env vars

R[5]:
  Always Observe→Act→Observe: call snapshot({ page }) before and after every action
  Never reuse aria-ref labels after navigation or DOM changes — re-snapshot first
  Use state object to persist data across -e calls within the same session
  Prefer snapshot() over screenshotWithAccessibilityLabels() for text inspection (fewer tokens)
  Use playwriter session reset <id> to recover from CDP disconnects without losing session

E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Navigate and snapshot","playwriter session new; playwriter -s 1 -e 'await page.goto(\"https://github.com\"); await snapshot({ page })'","Accessibility tree with aria-ref labels (e1, e2, ...) for each interactive element"
  "Click with label","playwriter -s 1 -e 'await page.locator(\"aria-ref=e3\").click(); await snapshot({ page })'","Page state after click; updated accessibility tree shows new UI state"
  "MCP setup","Add playwriter to mcpServers, restart the client, and ensure the target tab is green","AI agent can call execute tool with Playwright code; existing Chrome logins are available"
